tourBios.exmtStatus: Exempt - Finished 11-45 at 2015 Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament (exempt to second reshuffle)
tourBios.carHigh:
2015: Played in five events on the Web.com Tour and made two cuts.

2014: Finished T87 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December. 

2013: Missed the cut in all three Tour-related starts, the South Georgia Classic, the Stadion Classic at UGA and the John Deere Classic.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Began his collegiate career at the University of Mississippi before transferring to Missouri Baptist University in St. Louis. Won four events in college and was both a Ping All-America selection and an NAIA All-America.
tourBios.personal: Attended Marquette High in Chesterfield, Mo...Has two sisters. Twitter account is @cnaegel...If he weren't a pro golfer, he'd be a stock broker...Biggest thrill in golf was playing in the U.S. Amateur and in the 2013 John Deere Classic...Favorite course he's played is the Ocean Course at Kiawah Island. Says he would like to play Augusta National...Favorite teams are University of Mississippi and the St. Louis Cardinals. Albert Pujols is the most famous person he's met...Biggest single events he's attended were St. Louis Cardinals playoff and World Series games...Enjoys the TV show "The Big Bang Theory" and likes to vacation anywhere "on the water."...Not many people know he likes hockey...Would put his father, Tiger Woods and Jack Nicklaus in his dream foursome. His bucket list includes visiting Australia.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour in 2016 is T12th at the Servientrega Championship Presented by Efecty.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 25th in Driving Distance on the Web.com Tour.
